HAPPY BIRTHDAY SADASIUS!!!!!!!
Love you sooo much I think I must be crazy! ;p

I know I know, haven't posted in a while get off my back! :p
Well what to say?.... Got a raise! YAYS!!! The Christmas rush is keeping me busy but it's moving smoothly. Loving the busy rush and crabby people who want, want, want! Ya right....NOT! *rolls eyes* 

Working hard painting my ornaments that I give as gifts each year and as usual running out of time...can't mess with tradition! ;)
Feeling kinda blah cause I can't be with one of my friends right now. Her husbands father past away and I wish I could give her a huge hug!

Happier note, 2 friends I lost touch with a year ago came looking for me at my store. There expecting there second child and there's a card on its way to my old address with a pic of their son. I'm hoping someone will be nice enough to leave it by the mail boxes for me. Seeing them made me feel so happy, I was feeling a little under the weather when I sent out my cards I'd lost there address when I moved the first time. :( But now we're back in touch and I plan to keep it that way! :)

Good friends and the love of my life, I can't ask for any thing more! :)

Well yesterday I came home from work early with another one of my stupid migraines again. *Grssssies!* It felt good though being able to leave and without feeling guilty about it. Jen practically shoved me out the door cause I was afraid to leave her on her own in fear of not finding anyone to replace me. She told me no worries she'd be fine and to go home and get some rest! She's so awesome I'm so glad I got the chance to work with her!

I also got good news before I left from my District manager. She heard I wasn't feeling well and decided to call me before I left with news of our past mystery shop. We got 80% and it was either myself or Jen that got shopped. I was so relieved and happy to hear that, I've been so worried about our results and at least now I can finally relax about it. YAYS!!! :)
Dreading work on Monday already. I really don't want it to be finalized that my assistant will no longer be with me!

Today was silly, I went into Rideau for 7;30am to help set up a slipper kiosk Bentley's is putting in and my boss and I get there to find an empty space where it was suppose to be.*Groans* Apparently we found out later that the contractors who were putting it in changed the dates and we were never informed, that's head office for yeah! So now we have to go in and try it again tomorrow. Well at least I had a good day working for a bit in their store and I got a chance to have a chat with Jemstar before she started work. :) So all in all it wasn't so bad!  

Some changes are happening in my store next week, I am finally getting an assistant manager! I'm happy but nervous at the same time. Happy cause I need the help with Christmas and nervous on whether or not we'll get along. My boss says she is very nice and is a hard worker and with great customer service and she feels we'll get along great but even with her reassuring words I still can't help but be nervous. *Sighs* Oh well! With this change I am losing one of my girls though, I like her very much but it will be better for me in the long run. She has gotten rather lazy lately and her work ethics tend to suck and that is not someone I need on my team.

Christmas hours are starting as of the 5th of November and I'm not looking forward to them. The mall is repeating the same hours as last year and they obviously did not learn from their past mistake when there was no one in the mall before 9am and no one after 9pm. but still they set the same hours. *rolls eyes* It's all do to Sears being open early, because of them they feel the rest of the mall should open when they do. Well that's fine and dandy for Sears they are able to pull in the sales that early with there specials but as for the rest of the mall it's a ghost town. Oh well not much I can do about that.

Well at least I got away for the weekend before the Christmas rush starts. I had such an awesome time in Toronto and found the North Bound show very interesting and hope to go again next year!

Well a week of work is almost over and then I'm off to Toronto for few days with friends! YAYS! :)
Just hope this cold I woke up with won't get in the way. :(

Was woken up a few times last night by I think a party going on below me. A few times I awoke to people shouting but my favorite had to be the guy who chose to sing at the top of his lungs! He wasn't half bad but for some reason I still wanted to egg him! 
Oh well what can you do? At least I have the comfort of knowing I have two days off to catch up. :)

I came home to find Bob shedding all over and he's poohped all over his house!!!!! EWWWWS!!!!
Oh well that can't be as bad as the nest of baby spiders Sadasius found in one of my turtlenecks when we moved. :0 Now that was really gross! *squirms like little girl*

I recently chose to try and reinstate a friendship that I myself had ended. It was so weird like we never had stopped talking so I'm thinking this is a good sign. His girlfriend I know hates me but the feeling I can assure you is quite mutual. I had ended our friendship mostly because of her behavior towards me but I feel now that I may have given up to easily and throwing someone out of my life because his girlfriend doesn't like me now seems rather silly. I told him in response to him saying she hates me that that is her problem and that I still would like our friendship no matter what she thinks.
I know it will not be easy for him if we do become friends again as she will most definitely give him a hard time about it and I know it will restart her childish behavior yet again towards me but I am willing to put up and ignore her because friends do that. Now I did tell him that if he chooses not to then I will understand and respect his decision. I may not agree with it knowing he is doing it to keep her happy but when you love someone you'll do anything even if it means letting go of someone else you care about. I will except it though because I really don't want him to have to deal with her B.S again. 
It doesn't really sound fare to me though considering if she loves him she would do anything for him even if it means him being friends with someone she hates.
Any rate now I await the decision *sighs*....not much else I can do.

Well non top of lying awake for 2hrs after I finally fall asleep for an hour I am awoken by a nightmare. :( Haven't had one for a while....well except of course if you count the one I had sex with my ex...*Shudders at thought* This one was way more frightening! I drempt I was at home and some guys were breaking in. I ran into my room and locked the door and tried desperately to call for help but as I reached someone the line went dead. I sat silent for a moment paralyzed by fear  listening to where the intruders may be. Then a huge thud at my bedroom door and it started to break then a voice shouting we know you're in there prepare to die Bitch. Now tears streaming down my face I made for my window and managed to climb to my balcony just as my door gave way. I then climbed over the side of my balcony and some how swung myself to the one below me as gun shots rang out. I pounded franticly on the windows screaming for who ever would hear me. Finally a face appeared and opened the window and helped me inside then asking why I was there and what was going on? I told them and said we need to call 911! They just smiled an eerie unwelcoming grin and said don't you worry I'll take care of you! Now a new fear arising I tried to run but to no avail, the guy tackled me flipped me over and thats when I felt the knife and screamed....

Well after working everyday this week I was so glad my final day of this was over. Or at least I thought....When I came in to work that day I noticed a ceiling tile was droopy and there was a nice big water mark. I called security and they came to have a look and found no leak but put a bucket in the ceiling where it may have come from just in case....crises adverted or so I thought....At four when I was getting ready to leave another spot in the ceiling was dripping...*GROANS* so called security again.*sigh* They came down and sure enough there's deffinately a leak and I ended up staying till 5;30 waiting for the verdict on whether it was fixable, whether I'd have to stay after close or whether it was our A.C unit and then I have to wait till Monday to call head office to send someone to fix it.*rolls eyes* Apparently its the A.C some how the rain was getting into it and well now dripping into my store, so now I have a hole in my ceiling, have to keep the A.C off and play the waiting game! Oh well despite that I had a good day at work and we all enjoyed having the good looking security guards up in our ceiling. :P
My day ended nicely though I got to spend time with Jemstar and I quite enjoyed myself. It was so nice to finally get out after being cooped up all week and who better to spend it with!! :)

Well I decided enough was enough and I went to my ex's store this morning and asked when I could get my Play station and he said I could have it right now cause it has been in his back room for the past couple of months. I asked why he had'nt brought it down and he said it was because he just did'nt think about it......Ya right *rolls eyes dramatically* Any who's I finally got it back with out me being nasty and I kept my cool and told him thanks and much appreciated and went on my way.
Oh yeah he also said he liked my hair and I looked good! *rolls eyes again*
